law.text:
The Administration may not issue a permit for any outdoor sign along or near any federal-aid primary highway, if the sign:
Imitates or resembles any official traffic sign, signal, or device;
Is erected or maintained on any tree or painted or drawn on any rock or other natural feature;
Is erected or maintained in a way that:
Obscures or otherwise interferes with the effectiveness of an official traffic sign, signal, or device; or
Obstructs or interferes with a driver's view of approaching, merging, or intersecting traffic;
Is located within 250 feet of any public park, public forest, playground, or cemetery that is adjacent to a federal-aid primary highway; or
Is along or near a scenic byway located on the federal-aid primary highway.
